README.win32
------------

Compiling under win32 may be tricky...

Preferably you build this using MinGW (http://www.mingw.org/).  This
may for example be done in the following ways:
- natively under Windows using Cygwin (http://sources.redhat.com/cygwin/)
- natively under Windows MSYS (http://www.mingw.org/msys.shtml)
- Using a GNU/Linux (*nix) hosted cross compiler.
 (for example http://www.devolution.com/~slouken/SDL/Xmingw32/)

- Installer build: http://www.jrsoftware.org/isinfo.php



